[h1]Variables[/h1]

Now, let's assign a value to the variable and print it.
[code format="cpp" codeId="179"]#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
   [b]int [/b]myVariable = 10;
   [b]cout << myVariable;[/b]
   return 0;
}
// Outputs 10[/code]
[note]The C++ programming language is [b]case-sensitive[/b], so [b]myVariable [/b]and [b]myvariable [/b]are two different identifiers.[/note]

